  # Data, Information and Knowledge 
  
  ## Relational Data
  
  ### Data, Information and Knowledge 
  
  What is the difference between data, information and knowledge?
  
  Data are the raw bits and pieces of information with no context, knowledge is the consumption of information, and used to make 
  decisions. An informaion is fata that has been interpreted. 
  
  What would be the primary key in the customers and orders table?
  
  My database for a insurance company and my primary key would be a combination of their last name and birthday.
  So the first 4 letters of their last name last 3 of their first name and the last two numbers of their birth year.
  
  
  How would the customers and orders table be related?
  
  This unique ID will be able to related each person individually. 
  
  What would be the foreign key in the orders table?
  
  The foreign key would their user name that was created with their birhtday and first and last names. 
  
  
