  ## Structured Query Language
  
  Explain RDBMS and how it relates to SQL and the purpose of SQL
  
  RDBMS is Relational Database Management System which is a program that allow you to create, update and administer a relational 
  database, and this uses a SQl language to access the database. The purpose of SQL is that it is the programming language used
  to communicate with data stored in a relational database.
  
  The primary key in the example above is the customer ID . I think it is this because it is unique to that customer.
  
  ## SQL Injections
  
  SQL is input from the user that is not in the database and the database will run when it should not, this a security threat because
  then a hacker might get unauthorized access to people information. Using parameters is the best thing to remedy this problem. 
  
  # Ethical and Legal Implications 
  
  Explain the purpose of a "code of ethics" and why the ACM created a code for the computing discipline.
  
  A code of ethics is a document that outlines a set of acceptable behaviors. The ACM was created so every member will know what
  is expected of each other. It was also the admonition to honest and trustworthy. It also clarifies the acceptable standardsof behaviors 
  for a professional group. 

  Explain the difference between a code of ethics and AUP (acceptable use policies.)
  
  Many organizations that provide technology services to a group of constituents or the public require agreement to an acceptable 
  use policy (AUP) before those services can be accessed is a set of rules that are not as formal as a code as ethics and company
  will have this
  
   
  
  

  


